	<static-content language-id="en_US">&lt;p sab="1828"&gt; &lt;span sab="1829" style="font-size: 12px;"&gt;A Dynamic Data List is a user defined collection of records organized in a list, similar to a spreadsheet. The records in a Dynamic Data List are composed of various field types such as text, date, integer, check box, and so on. These records are known as Data Definitions in Liferay&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p align="LEFT" sab="1830" style="padding: 0in; border: currentColor; line-height: 140%; margin-bottom: 0in;"&gt; &amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p align="LEFT" sab="1831" style="padding: 0in; line-height: 140%; margin-bottom: 0in;"&gt; &lt;font color="#000000" sab="1832"&gt;&lt;font face="Arial, Helvetica, Verdana, sans-serif" sab="1833"&gt;&lt;font sab="1834" style="font-size: 9pt;"&gt;&lt;u sab="1835"&gt;&lt;span sab="1836"&gt;To create a Dynamic Data List&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p align="LEFT" sab="1837" style="padding: 0in; line-height: 140%; margin-bottom: 0in;"&gt; &lt;font color="#000000" sab="1838"&gt;&lt;font face="Arial, Helvetica, Verdana, sans-serif" sab="1839"&gt;&lt;font sab="1840" style="font-size: 9pt;"&gt;&lt;span sab="1841"&gt;Navigate to the Dynamic Data Lists portlet in control panel and select it. You will notice at the top of the Dynamic Data Lists screen an "Add" button and a "Manage Data Definitions" button. The "Add" button is used to create a new Dynamic Data List, and the " Manage Data Definitions" button is used to create a new Data Definition.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p align="LEFT" sab="1842" style="padding: 0in; border: currentColor; line-height: 140%; margin-bottom: 0in;"&gt; &amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p align="LEFT" sab="1843" style="padding: 0in; line-height: 140%; margin-bottom: 0in;"&gt; &lt;font color="#000000" sab="1844"&gt;&lt;font face="Arial, Helvetica, Verdana, sans-serif" sab="1845"&gt;&lt;font sab="1846" style="font-size: 9pt;"&gt;&lt;span sab="1847"&gt;First let's create a Data Definition:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;ul sab="1848"&gt; &lt;li sab="1849"&gt; &lt;p align="LEFT" sab="1850" style="padding: 0in; line-height: 140%; margin-bottom: 0in;"&gt; &lt;font color="#000000" sab="1851"&gt;&lt;font face="Arial, Helvetica, Verdana, sans-serif" sab="1852"&gt;&lt;font sab="1853" style="font-size: 9pt;"&gt;&lt;span sab="1854"&gt;Press the "Manage Data Definitions" buttons, then on the Data Definitions screen press the "Add" button.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;li sab="1855"&gt; &lt;p align="LEFT" sab="1856" style="padding: 0in; line-height: 140%; margin-bottom: 0in;"&gt; &lt;font color="#000000" sab="1857"&gt;&lt;font face="Arial, Helvetica, Verdana, sans-serif" sab="1858"&gt;&lt;font sab="1859" style="font-size: 9pt;"&gt;&lt;span sab="1860"&gt;From the New Data Definition screen, give the Data Definition a name and a description, then drag the fields you want to use in your data definition from the left side of the template to the right side. After dragging a field(s) to the right, double click on the field and you will notice the "Settings" tab will display on the left side of the window. Change any settings that you would like, such as field name and field width. When you are finished adding all of your fields, press the "Save" button to save the Data Definition.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;/ul&gt; &lt;p align="LEFT" sab="1861" style="padding: 0in; line-height: 140%; margin-bottom: 0in;"&gt; &lt;font color="#000000" sab="1862"&gt;&lt;font face="Arial, Helvetica, Verdana, sans-serif" sab="1863"&gt;&lt;font sab="1864" style="font-size: 9pt;"&gt;&lt;span sab="1865"&gt;Now let's create a Dynamic Data List:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;ul sab="1866"&gt; &lt;li sab="1867"&gt; &lt;p align="LEFT" sab="1868" style="padding: 0in; line-height: 140%; margin-bottom: 0in;"&gt; &lt;font color="#000000" sab="1869"&gt;&lt;font face="Arial, Helvetica, Verdana, sans-serif" sab="1870"&gt;&lt;font sab="1871" style="font-size: 9pt;"&gt;&lt;span sab="1872"&gt;Back on the "Dynamic Data Lists" screen, press the "Add" button to create a new Dynamic Data List. Give your new list a name and description, then click the "Select" link under the Data Definition text. From the Data Definitions screen select the Data Definition you created in the previous step.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;li sab="1873"&gt; &lt;p align="LEFT" sab="1874" style="padding: 0in; line-height: 140%; margin-bottom: 0in;"&gt; &lt;font color="#000000" sab="1875"&gt;&lt;font face="Arial, Helvetica, Verdana, sans-serif" sab="1876"&gt;&lt;font sab="1877" style="font-size: 9pt;"&gt;&lt;span sab="1878"&gt;Back in the "Dynamic Data Lists" screen add any workflow you would like to be applied to the items in the list, then press the "Save" button.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;/ul&gt; &lt;p align="LEFT" sab="1879" style="padding: 0in; border: currentColor; line-height: 140%; margin-bottom: 0in;"&gt; &amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p align="LEFT" sab="1880" style="padding: 0in; border: currentColor; line-height: 140%; margin-bottom: 0in;"&gt; &amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p align="LEFT" sab="1881" style="padding: 0in; line-height: 140%; margin-bottom: 0in;"&gt; &lt;font color="#000000" sab="1882"&gt;&lt;font face="Arial, Helvetica, Verdana, sans-serif" sab="1883"&gt;&lt;font sab="1884" style="font-size: 9pt;"&gt;&lt;u sab="1885"&gt;&lt;span sab="1886"&gt;To add a Dynamic Data List Display portlet to a page&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p align="LEFT" sab="1887" style="padding: 0in; line-height: 140%; margin-bottom: 0in;"&gt; &lt;font color="#000000" sab="1888"&gt;&lt;font face="Arial, Helvetica, Verdana, sans-serif" sab="1889"&gt;&lt;font sab="1890" style="font-size: 9pt;"&gt;&lt;span sab="1891"&gt;Now that you have created your Dynamic Data List you need to add a Dynamic Data List Display portlet to allow adding records to the list, and to display the list.&amp;nbsp;To add a Dynamic Data List Display to a page:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;ul sab="1892"&gt; &lt;li sab="1893"&gt; &lt;p align="LEFT" sab="1894" style="padding: 0in; line-height: 140%; margin-bottom: 0in;"&gt; &lt;font color="#000000" sab="1895"&gt;&lt;font face="Arial, Helvetica, Verdana, sans-serif" sab="1896"&gt;&lt;font sab="1897" style="font-size: 9pt;"&gt;&lt;span sab="1898"&gt;From the "Add" menu add a Dynamic Data List Display portlet to your page.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;li sab="1899"&gt; &lt;p align="LEFT" sab="1900" style="padding: 0in; line-height: 140%; margin-bottom: 0in;"&gt; &lt;font color="#000000" sab="1901"&gt;&lt;font face="Arial, Helvetica, Verdana, sans-serif" sab="1902"&gt;&lt;font sab="1903" style="font-size: 9pt;"&gt;&lt;span sab="1904"&gt;In your Dynamic Data List Display portlet, select the configuration (wrench) icon, then select "Configuration".&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;li sab="1905"&gt; &lt;p align="LEFT" sab="1906" style="padding: 0in; line-height: 140%; margin-bottom: 0in;"&gt; &lt;font color="#000000" sab="1907"&gt;&lt;font face="Arial, Helvetica, Verdana, sans-serif" sab="1908"&gt;&lt;font sab="1909" style="font-size: 9pt;"&gt;&lt;span sab="1910"&gt;From the configuration screen choose the Dynamic Data List that you created above, then press the "Save" button.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;li sab="1911"&gt; &lt;p align="LEFT" sab="1912" style="padding: 0in; line-height: 140%; margin-bottom: 0in;"&gt; &lt;font color="#000000" sab="1913"&gt;&lt;font face="Arial, Helvetica, Verdana, sans-serif" sab="1914"&gt;&lt;font sab="1915" style="font-size: 9pt;"&gt;&lt;span sab="1916"&gt;Back in the Dynamic Data List display portlet, you can now use the "Add Record" button to add records to your Dynamic Data List.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;/ul&gt; &lt;p align="LEFT" sab="1917" style="padding: 0in; border: currentColor; line-height: 140%; margin-bottom: 0in;"&gt; &amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p align="LEFT" sab="1918" style="padding: 0in; border: currentColor; line-height: 140%; margin-bottom: 0in;"&gt; &amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p align="LEFT" sab="1919" style="padding: 0in; border: currentColor; line-height: 140%; margin-bottom: 0in;"&gt; &lt;font sab="1920" style="font-size: 9pt;"&gt;&lt;font color="#000000" sab="1921"&gt;&lt;font face="Arial, Helvetica, Verdana, sans-serif" sab="1922"&gt;&lt;u sab="1923"&gt;&lt;span sab="1924"&gt;To configure the Dynamic Data List Display portlet&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;ul sab="1925"&gt; &lt;li sab="1926"&gt; &lt;p align="LEFT" sab="1927" style="padding: 0in; line-height: 140%; margin-bottom: 0in;"&gt; &lt;font color="#000000" sab="1928"&gt;&lt;font face="Arial, Helvetica, Verdana, sans-serif" sab="1929"&gt;&lt;font sab="1930" style="font-size: 9pt;"&gt;&lt;span sab="1931"&gt;From the Dynamic Data List portlet press the "Wrench" icon then select "Configuration". You will see the following options:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;ul sab="1932"&gt; &lt;li sab="1933"&gt; &lt;p align="LEFT" sab="1934" style="padding: 0in; line-height: 140%; margin-bottom: 0in;"&gt; &lt;font color="#000000" sab="1935"&gt;&lt;font face="Arial, Helvetica, Verdana, sans-serif" sab="1936"&gt;&lt;font sab="1937" style="font-size: 9pt;"&gt;&lt;span sab="1938"&gt;List Template: Allows you to select a different list template for displaying the list records.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;li sab="1939"&gt; &lt;p align="LEFT" sab="1940" style="padding: 0in; line-height: 140%; margin-bottom: 0in;"&gt; &lt;font color="#000000" sab="1941"&gt;&lt;font face="Arial, Helvetica, Verdana, sans-serif" sab="1942"&gt;&lt;font sab="1943" style="font-size: 9pt;"&gt;&lt;span sab="1944"&gt;Detail Template: Allows you to select a different detail template for adding records to the list.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;li sab="1945"&gt; &lt;p align="LEFT" sab="1946" style="padding: 0in; line-height: 140%; margin-bottom: 0in;"&gt; &lt;font color="#000000" sab="1947"&gt;&lt;font face="Arial, Helvetica, Verdana, sans-serif" sab="1948"&gt;&lt;font sab="1949" style="font-size: 9pt;"&gt;&lt;span sab="1950"&gt;Editable: Allows users to add records to the list.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;li sab="1951"&gt; &lt;p align="LEFT" sab="1952" style="padding: 0in; line-height: 140%; margin-bottom: 0in;"&gt; &lt;font color="#000000" sab="1953"&gt;&lt;font face="Arial, Helvetica, Verdana, sans-serif" sab="1954"&gt;&lt;font sab="1955" style="font-size: 9pt;"&gt;&lt;span sab="1956"&gt;Spreadsheet View: Allows users to view and add records in a spreadsheet view.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;/ul&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;/ul&gt; &lt;p align="LEFT" sab="1957" style="padding: 0in; line-height: 140%; margin-bottom: 0in;"&gt; &amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p align="LEFT" sab="1958" style="padding: 0in; line-height: 140%; margin-bottom: 0in;"&gt; &amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p align="LEFT" sab="1959" style="padding: 0in; line-height: 140%; margin-bottom: 0in;"&gt; &lt;font color="#000000" sab="1960"&gt;&lt;font face="Arial, Helvetica, Verdana, sans-serif" sab="1961"&gt;&lt;font sab="1962" style="font-size: 9pt;"&gt;&lt;u sab="1963"&gt;&lt;span sab="1964"&gt;To create a new List Template&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;ul sab="1965"&gt; &lt;li sab="1966"&gt; &lt;p align="LEFT" sab="1967" style="padding: 0in; line-height: 140%; margin-bottom: 0in;"&gt; &lt;font color="#000000" sab="1968"&gt;&lt;font face="Arial, Helvetica, Verdana, sans-serif" sab="1969"&gt;&lt;font sab="1970" style="font-size: 9pt;"&gt;&lt;span sab="1971"&gt;From the Dynamic Data List portlet select the "Add List Template" icon in the lower left corner of the portlet window.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;li sab="1972"&gt; &lt;p align="LEFT" sab="1973" style="padding: 0in; line-height: 140%; margin-bottom: 0in;"&gt; &lt;font color="#000000" sab="1974"&gt;&lt;font face="Arial, Helvetica, Verdana, sans-serif" sab="1975"&gt;&lt;font sab="1976" style="font-size: 9pt;"&gt;&lt;span sab="1977"&gt;From the Dynamic Data Mapping Screen:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;ul sab="1978"&gt; &lt;li sab="1979"&gt; &lt;p align="LEFT" sab="1980" style="padding: 0in; line-height: 140%; margin-bottom: 0in;"&gt; &lt;font color="#000000" sab="1981"&gt;&lt;font face="Arial, Helvetica, Verdana, sans-serif" sab="1982"&gt;&lt;font sab="1983" style="font-size: 9pt;"&gt;&lt;span sab="1984"&gt;Give your new list template a name and description.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;li sab="1985"&gt; &lt;p align="LEFT" sab="1986" style="padding: 0in; line-height: 140%; margin-bottom: 0in;"&gt; &lt;font color="#000000" sab="1987"&gt;&lt;font face="Arial, Helvetica, Verdana, sans-serif" sab="1988"&gt;&lt;font sab="1989" style="font-size: 9pt;"&gt;&lt;span sab="1990"&gt;In the "Language Type" list box select your template language type.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;li sab="1991"&gt; &lt;p align="LEFT" sab="1992" style="padding: 0in; line-height: 140%; margin-bottom: 0in;"&gt; &lt;font color="#000000" sab="1993"&gt;&lt;font face="Arial, Helvetica, Verdana, sans-serif" sab="1994"&gt;&lt;font sab="1995" style="font-size: 9pt;"&gt;&lt;span sab="1996"&gt;In the "Script" section enter the template script.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;li sab="1997"&gt; &lt;p align="LEFT" sab="1998" style="padding: 0in; line-height: 140%; margin-bottom: 0in;"&gt; &lt;font color="#000000" sab="1999"&gt;&lt;font face="Arial, Helvetica, Verdana, sans-serif" sab="2000"&gt;&lt;font sab="2001" style="font-size: 9pt;"&gt;&lt;span sab="2002"&gt;When finished press the "Save" button.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;/ul&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;/ul&gt; &lt;p sab="2003"&gt; &amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p sab="2004"&gt; &lt;u sab="2005" style="line-height: 15px; font-size: 12px;"&gt;&lt;span sab="2006"&gt;To create a new Detail Template&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;ul sab="2007"&gt; &lt;li sab="2008"&gt; &lt;p align="LEFT" sab="2009" style="padding: 0in; line-height: 140%; margin-bottom: 0in;"&gt; &lt;span sab="2010" style="font-size: 12px;"&gt;From the Dynamic Data List&amp;nbsp;portlet&amp;nbsp;select the "Add Detail Template" icon in the lower left corner of the&amp;nbsp;portlet&amp;nbsp;window.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;li sab="2011"&gt; &lt;p align="LEFT" sab="2012" style="padding: 0in; line-height: 140%; margin-bottom: 0in;"&gt; &lt;font color="#000000" sab="2013"&gt;&lt;font face="Arial, Helvetica, Verdana, sans-serif" sab="2014"&gt;&lt;font sab="2015" style="font-size: 9pt;"&gt;&lt;span sab="2016"&gt;From the Dynamic Data Mapping Screen:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;ul sab="2017"&gt; &lt;li sab="2018"&gt; &lt;p align="LEFT" sab="2019" style="padding: 0in; line-height: 140%; margin-bottom: 0in;"&gt; &lt;font color="#000000" sab="2020"&gt;&lt;font face="Arial, Helvetica, Verdana, sans-serif" sab="2021"&gt;&lt;font sab="2022" style="font-size: 9pt;"&gt;&lt;span sab="2023"&gt;Give your new detail template a name and description.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;li sab="2024"&gt; &lt;p align="LEFT" sab="2025" style="padding: 0in; line-height: 140%; margin-bottom: 0in;"&gt; &lt;font color="#000000" sab="2026"&gt;&lt;font face="Arial, Helvetica, Verdana, sans-serif" sab="2027"&gt;&lt;font sab="2028" style="font-size: 9pt;"&gt;&lt;span sab="2029"&gt;Select "Create" or "Edit" mode. This option will only allow deleting required fields in Edit mode.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;li sab="2030"&gt; &lt;p align="LEFT" sab="2031" style="padding: 0in; line-height: 140%; margin-bottom: 0in;"&gt; &lt;font color="#000000" sab="2032"&gt;&lt;font face="Arial, Helvetica, Verdana, sans-serif" sab="2033"&gt;&lt;font sab="2034" style="font-size: 9pt;"&gt;&lt;span sab="2035"&gt;Use the palette and canvas to modify the form fields in the same manner as in "Create a Data Definition".&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;li sab="2036"&gt; &lt;p align="LEFT" sab="2037" style="padding: 0in; line-height: 140%; margin-bottom: 0in;"&gt; &lt;font color="#000000" sab="2038"&gt;&lt;font face="Arial, Helvetica, Verdana, sans-serif" sab="2039"&gt;&lt;font sab="2040" style="font-size: 9pt;"&gt;&lt;span sab="2041"&gt;When finished press the "Save" button.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;/ul&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;/ul&gt;</static-content>
